<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7189> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7189" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Father and son. The father, an officer (#) under M. Antonius at Actium, was saved by the appeal of his son, who had been an officer there under Octavian (#, App. BC 4.42). As Appian means had commanded rather than had been a praetor in this context, the praetor of uncertain date, MRR 2.463, and Index, should be deleted. Mommsen suggests that the father may have been the M. Metellus who gave a gladiatorial show in 60 (Att. 2.1.1) and the son possibly Caecilius M. f. Metellus, pr. urb., procos. Sardiniae, named in CIL 10.7581 (EE 3.14). (TJC)[35x]\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6565> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6565" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A praetorius who saved his father, an Antonian supporter and a prisoner after Actium at Samos (App. BC 4.42)." .
